Subject: [PATCH] docs: add refs [17]-[20], fix per-feature academic gaps
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses per-feature prior art gaps identified in academic review:

[17] Christiansen — parametric EQ near Nyquist (cited by RBJ as more complete
     than Orfanidis; referenced inline in §2 decramping note, pending PDF)
[18] Zavalishin — The Art of VA Filter Design (TPT/trapezoidal theory that
     underpins the Simper SVF; cited in §2.2)
[19] RBJ AES 1994 — The Equivalence of Various Methods of Computing Biquad
     Coefficients (formally proves all biquad topologies have identical transfer
     functions; cited in §2.3 where we measure 0.000 dB difference)
[20] Zölzer DAFX — standard reference for coefficient update methods; cited in §7

Per-feature coverage is now:
  SVF topology      → [1] Simper, [18] Zavalishin, [19] RBJ Equivalence
  RBJ biquad        → [6] Cookbook, [19] Equivalence
  5-DOF / cramping  → [10] RBJ 2026, [11] Orfanidis, [17] Christiansen
  Real-time safety  → [4] Renn-Giles & Rowland
  Variable-cadence  → [7] Moore, [8] ISO 226, [20] Zölzer
  Phase vocoder     → [15] WASPAA 2001
  Wavetable synth   → [16] RBJ 1996
